The paper discusses deep neural network architectures and algorithms for vision and speech applications, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses large-scale industrial research and development efforts, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses challenges and recent successes in running deep neural networks on hardware-restricted platforms, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
